                                              We always focus on what we can control.<br>
What we do is minimize the impact of an unpredictable event if harmful, and maximize it if beneficial...<br>
The gains should be given a chance to grow <span size="2"><u><b>exponentially</b></u></span> while making "the losses" <span size="2"><u><b>predictable and linear.</b></u></span></p><p><span size="2"><span size="2">And that's the essence of </span><u><b>"adding to a winner."</b></u></span><br> <span size="2">A very counterintuitive concept, indeed.</span></p><u><b><span size="3">Rule Two</span></b></u><br> <u><b><span size="3">No Rebalancing or Restructuring before at least three (03) Units are Active.</span></b></u><p> 
